wormhole connects stanford and mit stanford engineering jump to navigation intranet click here to button navigation control click here to jump to soe search section header click here to jump to the top site navigation click here to jump to the left side site navigation click here to jump to the content click here to jump to the priority navigation click here to jump to the bottom footer wormhole connects stanford and mit jamie beckett nov 7 2011 stanford engineering students and faculty from stanford and mit can chat collaborate or even do lunch thanks to an innovative communications portal that connects two university cafes lunch crowds at mit can now enjoy a touch of california sunshine via a live video connection from stanford engineering's forbes family cafe to its counterpart at mit the wormhole which officially launched today is designed to encourage casual interactions by freeing participants from their laptops or special video conferencing rooms and placing them in a social setting senior associate dean for student affairs brad osgood connects via the wormhole with mit dean for student life chris colombo and bert and candee forbes at the forbes family cafe the device which looks like the cone of silence from the 1960s tv series and recent film get smart includes a high resolution video camera a flat screen and a set of advanced speakers and microphones the high quality audio was essential because unlike most video conferencing systems this has to work in a noisy cafe an identical wormhole is operating at mit the technology was designed by mit alum kevin brown named for the hypothetical shortcut through space time that could theoretically enable time travel the wormhole is currently open 24 7 without a reservation media contacts jamie beckett school of engineering 650.736 2241 jbeckett stanford edu stanford engineering stanford engineering imagine the future dean's office explore our facilities facts & figures history newsroom spotlight on engineering working